# Architecture

**Stack:** Vite, React 19, React Router v7 (`createBrowserRouter`). Not Next.js — no `app/` router or Server Actions. Shared conventions and the full stack table live in **[CURSOR.md](../../CURSOR.md)**.

## Folder Structure

```
src/
  main.tsx                      # createRoot, RouterProvider, global CSS import
  index.css                     # Design tokens (@theme), @utility (typo-*), layout-figma-frame
  vite-env.d.ts

  routes/
    index.tsx                   # RouteObject[], root layout (AppLayout + Outlet), path table

  pages/                        # Route-level screens (one default export per file)
    MainPage.tsx
    DesignSystemPage.tsx
    …

  features/                     # Domain features (primary place for feature-specific code)
    {feature}/                  # e.g. board, auth, mypage, home
      components/               # UI used only inside this feature
      hooks/                    # Feature hooks (optional)
      …                         # types, constants local to feature — only if small; else use src/types
      index.ts                  # Barrel: what pages/other features may import

  components/
    ui/                         # Design-system / shadcn-style shared UI (CVA + cn)
      index.ts
      …
    layout/                     # Shared chrome: Header, Footer, shells (optional)

  lib/
    api/                        # HTTP client + shared API helpers (axios target per CURSOR.md)
      client.ts
    cn.ts
    schemas/                    # Shared Zod (etc.) — optional

  stores/                       # Zustand global client state
  hooks/                        # Cross-feature React hooks (optional)
  types/                        # Cross-feature TypeScript types (optional)
  constants/                    # App-wide constants (optional)

  assets/
    icons/
      index.ts                  # Barrel for SVG (SVGR) exports (recommended)
      …

  providers/                    # App-level providers (e.g. QueryClientProvider)
```

Path alias **`@/`** → `src/` (Vite + TypeScript).

## Core Rules

### Component placement

| What | Where |
|------|--------|
| Feature-specific UI, hooks, small local modules | `features/{feature}/` (usually `components/` + `hooks/` under it) |
| Shared across multiple features | `components/ui/` |
| Cross-page layout chrome (header, footer, nav shell) | `components/layout/` |

Do **not** add parallel `components/board/`, `components/auth/`, etc. — that belongs under **`features/board/`**, **`features/auth/`**, etc.

### `index.ts` barrel re-exports

| Area | Barrel |
|------|--------|
| `components/ui/` | Required |
| `features/{feature}/` | Required for the public surface the rest of the app imports |
| `assets/icons/` | Recommended |

**No barrel required** for `routes/`, `pages/`, or most of `lib/**` unless you introduce a package-style submodule.

```ts
// Good
import { Button } from "@/components/ui";
import { BoardList } from "@/features/board";
import { LogoIcon } from "@/assets/icons";

// Bad (once barrels exist)
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
import { BoardList } from "@/features/board/components/BoardList";
```

### Data flow

| Concern | Tool / place |
|---------|----------------|
| Server state (fetch, cache, mutations) | TanStack Query + API helpers in `lib/api/` (feature code calls them or thin wrappers in `features/*/`) |
| Global client UI state | Zustand (`stores/`) |
| Local UI state | `useState` / `useReducer` in the component |

All browser HTTP should go through **one client style** (target: **axios**). Avoid ad-hoc `fetch` in pages; align with [CURSOR.md](../../CURSOR.md).

### Layout shell (mobile)

- `#root`: **`--width-app-shell` (430px)**; main column: **`layout-figma-frame`** / **`--width-figma-frame` (370px)** — `src/index.css`, [CURSOR.md](../../CURSOR.md).
- App-wide route layout: **`routes/index.tsx`** (`AppLayout` + `Outlet`).

### Admin (optional)

Admin root wrapper may set **`data-admin`** on its outer element when admin-only typography/tokens depend on it.

### Route organization (convention)

Use **path prefixes** and **nested `RouteObject`s** + layout `element`s:

| Intent | Typical approach |
|--------|------------------|
| Authenticated-only | Parent route + guard/loader + nested `children` |
| Public (landing, auth) | Sibling routes or branch under `/` |
| Main shell (header) | Layout route + `Outlet` for child paths |

Register routes in **`src/routes/index.tsx`**; page modules live under **`src/pages/`** and compose **`@/features/*`** + shared **`@/components/*`**.
